examples.en: She can't be telling lies.
Now, just listen to what I'm telling you.
I keep telling you, but you won't listen!
"Who is the letter from?" "I'm not telling."
I always know when he's telling lies.
He was enjoined by conscience from telling a lie.
How do we know you're telling the truth?
I am telling you this for your good. (A. S. Hornby)
Your father gave you a walloping for telling a lie.
Is she telling fibs again?
We all funked telling her the truth.
The story gets better with each telling.
She always digresses when telling a story.
That's no jokeing man, I'm telling you - jokeing apart!
Was he telling porkies again?
Sheppard was telling the truth.
They foxed me into telling the secret.
Don't go telling tales to the teacher!
Why are you telling such barefaced lies?
He eventually decided against telling her.
Twice she was on the verge of telling all.
It's no good telling him - he won't listen.

May God strike me dead if I'm telling a lie!
I'm only telling you this for your own good.
Who is the letter from? I'm not telling.
Hunger is nature's way of telling you to eat.
One questions whether he's telling the truth.

Telling the teacher was the right thing to do.
